<TITLE> 20 injured in train accident in Mymensingh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mymensingh, May 4 (bdnews24.com)  At least 20 people were injured when a train hit another from behind at the Mymensingh Railway Station early on Monday. Tthree railway carriages and the engine of the oncoming train were damaged in the collision. The accident also led to the failure of the station's communications system for about an hour, leading to a halt of all incoming and outgoing trains. A five-member investigation committee, headed by divisional transportation officer Nazmul Islam, has been formed. The committee has been asked to submit its report within three days. Mymensingh Railway Station super Nazrul Islam said that a Dhaka-bound train from Dewanganj hit a standing train from behind at a high speed at around 4.30am. At least 20 people, including Sobuj Hasan, 40, driver of the speeding train, were injured. Sobuj was admitted to Mymensingh Medical College Hospital with serious injuries. The others were given first aid. IIslam said that the train had entered the railway station five minutes ahead of the scheduled time without clearance. The accident had occurred as the driver apparently failed to control the train due to its high speed, he said. bdnews
